        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Screenshot-2026-02-15-at-14.55.35.png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=1.5&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 1.5dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Screenshot-2026-02-15-at-14.55.35.png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=1.75&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 1.75dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Screenshot-2026-02-15-at-14.55.35.png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=2&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 2dppx)">
        
      </picture>

        <figcaption>
          <span>Image credit: <cite>Bloober Team</cite></span>
        </figcaption>
  </figure>
  </p>

    

</header>
  <div data-component="article-content">



            <p><a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/companies/bloober-team">Bloober Team</a>'s countdown to Valentine's Day has ended, and despite all those rose references, it's not a Rule of Rose revival, but is, in fact, <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/layers-of-fear">Layers of Fear</a> 3.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/bloober-team-rose-teaser-countdown">While the website had spurred all kinds of theories</a> – for instance, taking the capital letters from the word salad on the site "RemosdNeulSerorehsoOvamCeyerd" is an anagram of "Cronos", leading some to speculate that this was a teaser for DLC for <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/cronos-the-new-dawn">Cronos: The New Dawn</a> – Bloober has marked the tenth anniversary of the horror game with confirmation of a third instalment.</p>
<figure>
<p>
<a aria-label="Layers of Fear | Special Event | “The Sick Rose” | Announcement" data-platform="youtube" href="https://www.youtube.com/embed/VxU-9A3tw80?autoplay=1" onclick="((e) => { e.preventDefault(); e.currentTarget.closest('.video_wrapper').innerHTML = e.currentTarget.querySelector('template').innerHTML; enableElements(); })(event)" title="Click to play video from YouTube">
<span>Layers of Fear | Special Event | “The Sick Rose” | Announcement</span>
<template>
<iframe allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen="" data-src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/VxU-9A3tw80?autoplay=1" frameborder="0" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/VxU-9A3tw80?autoplay=1" title="Layers of Fear | Special Event | “The Sick Rose” | Announcement">
</iframe> </template>
</a>
</p>
<figcaption>Layers of Fear | Special Event | “The Sick Rose” | Announcement.<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VxU-9A3tw80" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Watch on YouTube</a></figcaption></figure>
<p>There was no gameplay to showcase, I'm afraid, but we were treated to a strange live-action teaser, embedded above, in which we were told "the door won't stay closed". Unfortunately, there's no other information, either, such as a release date.</p>
<p>Though entitled Layers of Fear 3, this is actually the fourth Layers of Fear game, as the original game was remade for current-gen systems in 2023.</p><figure>
 


<figcaption><span>Image credit: <cite>Bloober Team</cite></span></figcaption>
</figure>
<p>Bloober's been on a good run. It's already released <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/silent-hill-2-remake">Silent Hill 2 Remake</a>, Cronos: The New Dawn, and a <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/platforms/switch-2">Switch 2</a> version of Layers of Fear called Layers of Fear: The Final Masterpiece Edition, and is also working on Silent Hill 1 Remake and Project M, a horror game published by Broken Mirror Games exclusively on Nintendo Switch.</p><p>While I loved the settings and imagery, I ultimately didn't get on with the previous sequel <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/layers-of-fear-2">Layers of Fear 2</a>, labelling it <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/layers-of-fear-2-eagerly-anticipated-horror-sequel-falls-flat">a slick psychological horror plagued by poor pacing and infuriating instakills</a> when I reviewed it back in 2019. I similarly <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/blair-witch-review-lumpy-horror-that-has-its-fair-share-of-scares">struggled with Blair Witch</a>, and though I enjoyed <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/the-medium-review">The Medium's aesthetics and mysterious storyline</a>, its finale contains some, uh, troubling narrative choices. I have, however, very much enjoyed the team's later output, including Silent Hill 2 Remake, <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/silent-hill-2-remake-review">which received a rare 5/5 from me,</a> and Cronos: The New Dawn.</p>

        </div>

  
